> 直击现场。
Running straight to the scene.
连载·黄冈日记④｜闲置多年的传染病医院紧急启用。
LianZai Huang Gang's diary, the infectious disease hospital that had been idle for years, went into emergency use.
特邀作者 杨梅 程定琴 徐志礼 梦轩 金昊 叶薇 澎湃新闻记者 方岸 杜心羽 吴佳颖 实习生 李佳悦 整理。
Invited author Yang Mei-ding Qin Xu Zhili Mengxuan Jin Hao Ye Wei Po journalist Fang Xin Yu Wu Jia Ying intern Li Jiayue tidy up.
2020-03-09 07:25 来源：澎湃新闻。
2020-03-09 07: 25 Source: news surging.
字号。
The font size.
超大。
Extremely large.
大。
Big.
标准。
Standards.
小。
Small.
【专题】防控新冠肺炎。
Topic: Prevention and control of new crown pneumonia.
连载·黄冈日记③｜两位患者：咳嗽多日都当感冒在应付。
less than one + less + less + less than + less than +: Coughing has been coping with a cold for days.
连载·黄冈日记②｜科室住满新冠肺炎患者，5位同事被感染。
Liu Zai Huang Gang's diary, full of patients with Newly crowned Pneumonia, 5 colleagues were infected.
连载·黄冈日记①｜“穿防护服戴口罩和护目镜”的人突然来了。
The man in protective clothing, masks, and goggles suddenly appeared.
【编者按】新冠病毒给湖北乃至全国带来一场危机，黄冈是这场疫情的重灾区之一。
The new crown virus brings a crisis to Hubei and even to the whole country. Huanggang is one of the hardest hit areas of the epidemic.
在这场战役中，黄冈人经历了旁观-卷入-创伤-斗争-反思的过程。
In this battle, the Huanggang people experienced the process of watching-involved-traumatizing-fighting-introspection.
我们用亲历者日记连载的形式，试图纵深还原疫情侵袭下的黄冈这60天。
We tried to restore Huanggang to 60 days under the attack of the epidemic in the form of a diary series of relatives.
1月18日，黄冈市决定，将空置备用的黄冈市传染病医院改造成新冠肺炎病例集中隔离治疗医院。
On January 18, the city of Huanggang decided to convert the empty Huanggang infectious disease hospital into a centralized quarantine hospital for cases of Newcrown Pneumonia.
三天时间，负责改造的黄冈市中心医院近百名职工加班加点完成任务。
Three days, responsible for the renovation of the Huanggang City Central Hospital nearly 100 staff working overtime to complete the task.
黄冈市卫健委也下发文件，抽调黄冈市下属各市县医院的部分医疗力量支援全市新冠肺炎诊疗工作。
Huanggang City Health Committee also issued documents, the transfer of Huanggang City hospitals some of the medical support of the city's new crown pneumonia diagnosis and treatment.
（斜体字内容为编辑所加，下同）医护人员从黄冈市中心医院向传染病医院转移设备设施【杨梅：黄冈市中心医院呼吸内科护士】1月21日上午接到通知，明天科室所有人要跟病人一起转到传染病医院（黄冈市二医院），护士长让我们与家人做好沟通，准备好生活用品。
Medical staff transfer equipment from Huanggang Central Hospital to the Infectious Diseases Hospital [Yangmei: Nursing Department of Respiratory Medicine of Huanggang Central Hospital] January 21 morning was notified that tomorrow all the staff would be transferred to the Infectious Diseases Hospital (Huanggang No. 2 Hospital) with their patients.
1月22日今天本来按照排班是中班，白天在家里休息。
January 22 Today was supposed to be a shift, with a day off at home.
上午在家将自己的生活用品打包好，跟公公婆婆简单交待了一下，让他们在家里好好的照顾自己和女儿，戴好口罩，不要跟别人多接触，尽量不出门。
At home in the morning to pack their daily necessities, with my mother-in-law told them to take good care of themselves and their daughter at home, wear masks, do not contact with others, try not to go out.
吃过中饭，一个人拖着行李去了黄州，临走前，女儿还问我“妈妈要什么时候回家”。
After lunch, a man dragged his luggage to Huangzhou. Before he left, my daughter asked me when my mother would like to go home.
因为答应过她，一年级期末考试如果考了一百分就带她坐飞机去海南看海。
Because promised her, if the final exam of the first grade took her to Hainan by plane to see the sea.
她努力考了一百分，可是这个寒假不能陪她去海南了。
She made an effort to get a hundred marks, but she can't accompany her to Hainan this winter vacation.
我也不知道会要多久能回家，只能乐观地跟她说，过半个月，没有那么多的病人，妈妈就回来了。
I didn't know how long it would take to get home, so I told her optimistically that in half a month, without so many patients, my mother would be back.
下午三点多，接到科室通知，让我们所有的人去科室帮忙转送病人。
More than three in the afternoon, received the department notice, let all of us go to the department to help transfer patients.
带上行李，下午四点到科室，换上工作服，跟科室的伙伴们一起帮病人清理物品，打包药品，清理科室物资……忙碌了几个小时，病人开始陆续转移去传染病医院。
Take your bags, come to the office at 4: 00 p. m., change into work clothes, help patients with office cleaning, pack drugs, clean up the department supplies... For hours, the patients began to move to the infectious diseases hospital.
匆匆吃过晚饭，护士长让我先去二医院帮忙。
After a hasty dinner, the head nurse asked me to go to the second hospital to help.
说实话，我的心里是忐忑的，之前从来没有去过二医院，不知道里面的布局如何，也不知道安排我们住宿的地点在哪里。
To tell the truth, my heart is perturbed, has never been to the second hospital, do not know the layout of the inside, do not know where to arrange our accommodation.
一路导航过去，终于在21：30左右赶到了二医院。
Navigated all the way to the second hospital at about 21: 30.
提着工作服，跟门卫说了一下是护士就进去了。
Holding his overalls, he told the doorman it was the nurse who went in.
楼道里，堆着各种物品，还有还不及清理的垃圾，到处像是在走迷宫，兜兜转转，寻寻觅觅，都不知道自己应该去哪里。
The hallway was a labyrinth of things piled up and less than cleared of rubbish, and it was like walking around in labyrinth, scouting around looking for it, not knowing where to go.
终于，在三楼的办公室里看到了我们护理部的熊主任，这个点了，才在吃早已冰冷的晚饭，她看到我进来，立即丢下筷子，给我安排工作。
Finally, in the third floor of the office to see our head bear, this point, is already eating cold dinner, she saw me come in, immediately dropped chopsticks, to arrange my work.
原来二医院这边的护士都是下面各县派过来支援的，但很多都不是我们呼吸专科的护士，为了病人的安全及护理工作的顺利开展，我们要一起共同开展工作。
The nurses on this side of the Second Hospital had been sent to support us by the counties below, but many of them were not nurses in our breathing department. We had to work together for the safety and care of patients.
根本没有时间让我熟悉环境，我立马换上防护服，开始了我的二医院的第一个通宵值守。
There was no time to acquaint myself with my surroundings, so I changed into protective gear and began my first overnight duty at my second hospital.
开始在传染病医院工作【程定琴：黄冈市中心医院呼吸内科护士】1月22日此次临时启用的传染病医院（又叫二医院）在遗爱湖边，我们呼吸内科所有病人都要转移过去。
Began to work in an infectious disease hospital [Cheng Ding-qin: Respiratory Nurse, Huanggang Central Hospital] January 22 The temporary opening of the infectious disease hospital (also known as the Second Hospital) at Lok Lakeside, where all our patients in the Department of Respiratory Medicine will be transferred.
转运病人真是一件费时费力的事。
Transporting patients is really a time-consuming task.
病情轻的病人，一辆救护车每次可以转四五个人，病情重的一次就只能转运一位，病人需要卧床，需要使用呼吸机或者高流氧治疗仪。
For patients with mild illness, an ambulance can take four or five people at a time. In serious cases, only one person can be transferred at a time. Patients need to stay in bed and need a ventilator or a high-flow oxygen therapy unit.
等候车辆的间隙，我们护士抽空整理打包病人的药物，以及科室常用的医用用品。
As we waited for the car to break, our nurses took time to pack the patient's medication, as well as the department's usual medical supplies.
想到废弃的医院物资稀缺，想到这是一场持久战，我们把平常在科室觉得好用的、以后在二医院用得上的物品统统都打包了，整整十几大袋。
Thinking of the scarcity of abandoned hospital supplies and the protracted war, we packed up a dozen or so bags of things we would normally find useful in a department and later in hospital.
十几包的重物全是我们几位护士一个个抬到一楼，搬上救护车。
Dozens of bags of heavy goods were carried one by one by our nurses to the ground floor and onto the ambulance.
一直到凌晨五点半，我们彭金娥护士长才把最后一位病人安全地送上了救护车，至此才完成了所有病人的转运工作。
It was not until half-past five in the morning that we, Sister Peng Kin-ngo, safely took the last patient to an ambulance, and thus completed the transfer of all the patients.
呼吸内科所有的医护人员也都跟随患者，作战地点由黄冈市中心医院呼吸内科转移到了二医院。
All the staff of the Department of Respiratory Medicine followed the patients, and the operation was transferred from the Department of Respiratory Medicine of Huanggang Central Hospital to the Second Hospital.
我们自己的行囊也搬至距离二医院步行十五分钟的盛捷酒店，此后就以此为“家”，开启了跟新型冠状病毒继续死磕的持久战。
We also moved our own bags to Shengjie Hotel, 15 minutes' walk from the Second Hospital, and then used it as a home for a protracted fight against the new coronavirus.
1月23日我们早早吃完早餐来到二医院准备上班。
January 23rd We finished our breakfast early and went to the Second Hospital to get ready for work.
来到二医院我们都傻眼了，这里的条件差到想哭，地面墙面污渍斑驳，到处垃圾脏兮兮的。
We were all silly when we got to the Second Hospital, where the conditions were so bad that we wanted to cry, the floors were stained and dirty with rubbish.
我真的不敢想象昨晚转过来的患者是怎么接受这一切的，他们怎么度过这一晚的。
I really can't imagine how the patient who turned around last night accepted all this and how they got through the night.
抱怨没有任何意义，只得默默换好防护服，着手准备上班。
There was no point in complaining, so I had to quietly change my suit and get ready for work.
转过来的病人分成了三个楼层，分别是二病区、三病区、四病区。
The patients were divided into three floors: two, three and four.
我们呼吸内科的原班人马，加上从罗田、英山、黄梅过来的支援人员。
Our original staff of Respiratory Medicine, plus the support staff from Luotian, Yingshan and Huangmei.
当时病情较重的大部分集中在三病区，所以三病区的人手相对多一些。
At that time, most of the severe cases were concentrated in the three disease areas, so the three disease area relatively more hands.
我和来自罗田县的何君和李金三个人负责四病区的20个病人。
I and three people from Luotian county, He Jun and Li Jin are in charge of 20 patients in the four-disease area.
可怕的是这里连呼叫铃都没有，也就是说，病人有什么事除了靠扯着喉咙喊，没有其他方式通知我们。
Terrible is the fact that there is no call-bell, that is to say, there is nothing the patient can do but yell at his throat and inform us otherwise.
所我们只好不停地一个个病房巡视，怕病人有什么突发状况发现不及时，不能及时处理。
So we have to constantly patrol one ward after another, afraid of patients have a sudden discovery not in time, can not be timely.
我们认定一个宗旨，忙乱可以，但不允许出错。
We believe that a purpose, busy can be, but not allowed to make mistakes.
我们一一核对清楚病人的姓名，以及需用药的药名。
We checked the names of the patients and the names of the medicines to be used.
到下午快2点才完成所有病人的输液。
It's almost 2: 00 p. m. to complete all patient transfusions.
接下来又是不休止地换药，拔针。
And then there was the endless change of medicine and the pulling of needles.
中途午饭送来的时候，我们以最快速度发送到每一个病人手上，让他们趁热吃，因为我们知道这里连微波炉都没有。
When lunch was delivered, we sent it as fast as we could to every patient and let them eat it hot, because we knew there was no microwave.
忙完一天才发现，我们竟然都忘了自己没喝水，没吃饭。
Busy day before we found out that we even forgot that they did not drink water, did not eat.
下班脱下防护服时，衣服全都汗湿了。
My clothes were all wet when I took off my protective clothing after work.
上班忙得热，病人却都一个个喊冷，只能不停给他们加被子。
Busy work, the patients are one after another called cold, can only keep adding quilts to them.
因为这里要么没空调，要么空调坏了。
Because there is no air conditioning or the air conditioner is broken.
我们向上面反映，下午就安排了专业人员过来维修空调和线路，努力给病人提供一个好的环境。
As we have shown above, professional staff have been assigned in the afternoon to repair the air conditioners and lines in an effort to provide a good environment for patients.
传染病医院比较简陋杂乱的环境【徐志礼：麻城市人民医院呼吸内科副主任】1月22日经过两天快速培训，今天，我们被安排到黄冈市惠民医院，正式参加新型冠状病毒的肺炎诊疗工作。
Hospital for Infectious Diseases is in a rudimentary and chaotic environment [Xu Zhili: Deputy Director of Respiratory Medicine, Massachusetts People's Hospital] On January 22, after two days of intensive training, we were assigned to Huimin Hospital in Huimin, Huanggang City, to participate in the diagnosis and treatment of the new coronavirus.
其它首批轮训的医护人员分别来自红安、英山、罗田、黄梅等县市，也被分至其它新冠肺炎救治点。
The other first batch of nurses came from Hongan, Yingshan, Luotian and Huangmei counties, and were also treated with the new crown pneumonia.
